The linear functional `cfc_toLinearFunctional ha x y` is defined as `compSL C(spectrum ℂ a, ℂ) _ _ _ _ (toLinearFunctional x y) (cfcCLM ha)`.
This means for any `g : C((spectrum ℂ a), ℂ)`, `(cfc_toLinearFunctional ha x y) g = ⟪x, (cfcCLM ha g) y⟫_ℂ`.
Since `cfcCLM ha` is an isometry (`norm_cfcHom`), `‖cfc_toLinearFunctional ha x y g‖ = ‖x‖ * ‖y‖ * ‖g‖`.
This is `cfc_toLinearFunctional_bound`.

The measure `cfc_toComplexMeasure ha x y` is defined as `ComplexRMK.rieszMeasure (cfc_toLinearFunctional ha x y)`.
The Riesz-Markov-Kakutani theorem states that for a continuous linear functional `L` on `C(X)`, there exists a measure `μ` such that `L(g) = ∫ g dμ` for all `g`.
The norm of the functional `L` is equal to the total variation of the measure `μ`.

So, `‖cfc_toLinearFunctional ha x y‖ = (cfc_toComplexMeasure ha x y).variation Set.univ`.
We know `‖cfc_toLinearFunctional ha x y‖ ≤ ‖x‖ * ‖y‖`.
Therefore, `(cfc_toComplexMeasure ha x y).variation Set.univ ≤ ‖x‖ * ‖y‖`.

